The paper deals with error correction codes and their decoding algorithms, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.CC) subfields of computer science. The paper also discusses the performance of the decoding algorithm in terms of error floors, which is a topic of interest in the subfield of discrete structures (cs.DS). The proposed algorithm can be applied to various types of product codes, including staircase, braided, and half-product codes, which are studied in the subfield of signal processing (cs.SI) and network information theory (cs.NI).
